🏸 Naive Bayes Badminton Prediction
📌 Overview

This project implements a Naive Bayes classification model to predict whether a game of badminton should be played based on weather conditions.

The dataset includes environmental factors such as:

Outlook
Temperature
Humidity
Wind

The target variable:

Play_Badminton (Yes/No)
📂 Dataset

The dataset used: badminton_dataset.csv

Features:
Feature	Description
Outlook	Weather condition (Sunny, Overcast, Rain)
Temperature	Temperature level
Humidity	Humidity level
Wind	Wind condition (Weak/Strong)
Target:
Column	Description
Play_Badminton	Whether to play (Yes/No)
⚙️ Workflow
1. Data Loading
import pandas as pd
b = pd.read_csv("badminton_dataset.csv")
2. Data Exploration
Checked missing values
Viewed dataset info
Generated statistical summary
3. Data Preprocessing
Converted categorical values to numerical using Label Encoding
from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder
l = LabelEncoder()
for i in b.columns:
    if b[i].dtype == "object":
        b[i] = l.fit_transform(b[i])
4. Feature Selection
x = b[["Outlook", "Temperature", "Humidity", "Wind"]]
y = b["Play_Badminton"]
5. Train-Test Split
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(
    x, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=42
)
6. Model Training

Model used: Multinomial Naive Bayes

from sklearn.naive_bayes import MultinomialNB
model = MultinomialNB()
model.fit(x_train, y_train)
7. Prediction
y_pred = model.predict(x_test)
8. Evaluation Metrics
Accuracy Score
Confusion Matrix
Classification Report
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, classification_report, confusion_matrix

print("Accuracy:", accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred))
print(confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred))
print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred))
📊 Results
The model predicts whether badminton should be played based on weather conditions.
Performance is evaluated using standard classification metrics.

(Exact accuracy depends on dataset size and split)

🧠 Algorithm Used
Naive Bayes Classifier
Based on Bayes' Theorem
Assumes independence between features
Suitable for categorical data
🚀 How to Run
Install dependencies:
pip install pandas scikit-learn
Place dataset in the same directory:
badminton_dataset.csv
Run the notebook or script.
